com.i2group.apollo.searchservice.transport

Class SearchNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.apollo.searchservice.transport.SearchNode

  • public class SearchNode
extends Object
    A set of criteria that an Entity or a Link must match in order to be returned by a dumbbell or network search.
    Since:
    3.0

      SearchNode()
      Constructs a new SearchNode, initializing all mandatory fields.

      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      FilterInfoList getFilterInfos()
      Gets the FilterInfoList containing the FilterInfos that an Item matching this SearchNode must conform to.
      ItemTypeIdList getItemTypeIds()
      Gets the ItemTypeIdList containing the type identifiers that Items matching this SearchNode must have.
      ScopeFilter getScopeFilter()
      Gets the ScopeFilter that defines the scope within which the search for matching Items takes place.
      String getSearchString()
      Gets the String used in determining whether an Item matches this SearchNode.

        public String getSearchString()

      • getScopeFilter

        public ScopeFilter getScopeFilter()
        Gets the ScopeFilter that defines the scope within which the search for matching Items takes place.
        Returns:
        See above, or null if the search should look for matches across the whole Analysis Repository.

      • getItemTypeIds

        public ItemTypeIdList getItemTypeIds()
        Gets the ItemTypeIdList containing the type identifiers that Items matching this SearchNode must have.
        Returns:
        See above, or null if the search should not restrict results to Items of particular types.

      • getFilterInfos

        public FilterInfoList getFilterInfos()
        Gets the FilterInfoList containing the FilterInfos that an Item matching this SearchNode must conform to.
        Returns:
        See above, or null if this SearchNode is not restricted to matching FilterInfos.
